%-- Cells with allocentric properties have been found in the hippocampal formation of both freely-moving rats (Taube, Muller, & Ranck, 1990; O’Keefe & Dostrovsky, 1971) and monkeys (Rolls & O’Mara, 1995; Ono, Nakamura, Nishijo, & Eifuku, 1993), as well as in the rat retrosplenial cortex (Chen, Lin, Green, Barnes, & McNaughton, 1994; McNaughton, Leonard, & Chen, 1989), but also in the monkey’s posterior parietal cortex (Snyder, Grieve, Brotchie, & Andersen, 1998).

